-- Tottenham Defeats Aston Villa 2-0 in England’s Premier League
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2013-10-20T17:06:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-10-20/tottenham-defeats-aston-villa-2-0-in-england-s-premier-league.html
Tottenham won 2-0 at Aston Villa
today in English soccer’s Premier League with goals from Andros
Townsend and Roberto Soldado.  Townsend opened the scoring in the 31st minute when his
cross from the right went into the net at the far post. Soldado
got the second goal in the 69th minute after Paulinho set up the
chance with a quick pass.  The result moves Tottenham up to fifth in the standings.
Arsenal leads with 19 points, followed by Chelsea and Liverpool
on 17, and Manchester City and Tottenham on 16.  Yesterday, Arsenal beat Norwich 4-1 and Chelsea defeated
Cardiff by the same score. Everton had a 2-1 win over Hull and
defending champion Manchester United drew 1-1 with Southampton.
Newcastle tied 2-2 with Liverpool, West Brom drew 0-0 at Stoke,
Swansea routed Sunderland 4-0 and Manchester City won 3-1 at
West Ham.  Crystal Palace hosts Fulham tomorrow.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
